\section*{Summative Assessment}

\begin{enumerate}

\item In Fig., $AB$ is a tangent to the circle with centre $O$ at the point $B$. $OC$ is perpendicular to $AB$. If $AB = 12$ cm and $OB = 5$ cm, find the length of $OC$.

\item From a point outside a circle, two tangents are drawn. Prove that the lengths of the tangents drawn from an external point to a circle are equal.

\item Two pipes running together can fill a tank in $11\frac{1}{9}$ minutes. If one pipe takes 1 minute more than the other to fill the tank separately, find the time in which each pipe would fill the tank separately.

\item From a point on the ground, the angle of elevation of the top of a tower is observed to be $30^\circ$. From a point 5 m vertically above the first point of observation, the angle of elevation of the top of the tower is $60^\circ$. Find the height of the tower and its horizontal distance from the point of observation.

\item Draw a triangle with sides $4$ cm, $5$ cm and $6$ cm. Then draw another triangle whose sides are $\frac{4}{5}$ of the corresponding sides of the first triangle.

\item A number $x$ is selected at random from the numbers $1, 2, 3, 4$ and another number $y$ is selected at random from the numbers $1, 2, 3, 4, 5$. Find the probability that the value of $xy$ is more than $6$.

\end{enumerate}




